Heat grill. Season steak with salt and pepper. Place steak on grill. Cover and cook over medium-high heat 4 minutes on each side. Turn again and cook 2 to 4 minutes on each side or until desired doneness. Let rest while preparing remainder of salad. Toss salad with 1/2 cup of the dressing. Arrange on platter. Arrange tomato wedges over top. Slice steak into 1/4-inch slices; arrange down center of platter. Drizzle with remaining 1/4 cup dressing and sprinkle with cheese.